"{\n  \"text\": \"This is how we make compost. The first thing we do is we show up with a bunch of blue drums full of rotten vegetables that we picked up from various kitchens and old produce that we got from Produce Marts. And then we cover it with leaves like that, and that's going to basically create a carbon and nitrogen layer that they can the bacteria can bond together to create the soil. Then we're going to add more rotten vegetables on top of the leaves. We're doing a lasagna-style compost pile. And that means that layering compost or carbon with nitrogen with nitrogen with carbon, all this and that. The final thing we're going to do is we're going to carbon cap it with some of the old dirt that didn't get hot enough for us. So we're going to reuse that because it was too carbon rich when we put it together. So we're just going to throw that on top of everything. And what it's going to look like at the very end after we all smooth it all out and get it all ready to go is this. It's about knee high. It's spread out over about 20 by 20, and we're going to get a tractor in about a week to form it like this. This is our aerated static pile that's all going very hot. And then over here was the old pile that didn't get hot enough. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" This is how we make compost.\",\n      \"start\": 0.48,\n      \"end\": 2.08,\n      \"duration\": 1.6,\n      \"confidence\": 0.997,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" This\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.998\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" is\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" how\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n   